sentences: Ernest Roland Ball (July 22, 1878 – May 3, 1927) was an American singer and songwriter, most famous for composing the music for the song "When Irish Eyes Are Smiling" in 1912.
He became a charter member of ASCAP in 1907, and wrote many American standards.
Ball was posthumously inducted into the Songwriters Hall of Fame in 1970.
Sheet Music for "Let the Rest of the World Go By"; music by Ernest R. Ball; lyrics by J. Keirn Brennan, M. Witmark & Sons publisher, 1919.
A 1944 musical Irish Eyes Are Smiling told the story of Ball's career and starred Dick Haymes and June Haver.
